[1]
Date: 3 Jun 2013
Source: Rai News 24 [machine trans., edited]
http://www.rainews24.it/it/news.php?newsid=178492


[Novel coronavirus - MERS-CoV], a dozen are positive without symptoms. Samples have been sent to ISS for confirmation

"Approximately a dozen people have tested positive" for the [novel coronavirus - MERS-CoV] "but are completely asymptomatic. We sent samples to the Institute of Medicine 'for confirmation'," says Professor Alessandro Bartoloni, head of infectious diseases at the AOU Careggi

"People with positive screening results" - continued the professor - "have not been isolated and are at home 'cause they have no signs. [We] continue to take samples and examine them to understand the extent to which the virus [is being transmitted] and' widespread '. The behavior of [the novel coronavirus - MERS-CoV] seems to have surprised the experts. "There was a belief, as indicated by the World Health [Organization]'- continues the infectious disease [specialist] - that the virus had limited transmission [person-to-person] and that infection led to aggressive disease. What we're seeing so far seems to be just the opposite -- widespread transmission and minimal to no disease. The scheme is 'reversed'.

The tests have been conducted on people who have had contact with someone who already 'is positive, although not presenting any symptoms. "In addition to the protection of persons - says Professor Bartoloni - this study will serve 'to figure out what is going on... The question at this point if whether the virus has been modified or if we are dealing with a totally different virus.

