[If the positive tests are confirmed by the Institute of Medicine, this will represent the 1st documentation of asymptomatic transmission of the MERS-CoV among contacts of clinically ill patients. The question raised by the presenting physician as to whether they are identifying a changed virus or whether they are identifying a different virus from the virus that has been associated with an apparently high case fatality rate is a good question. Another curious observation is that these positive specimens were obtained from throat swabs, and not lower respiratory tract specimens. Another difference from what has been observed up to the present. We await further information on this announcement.

It is not in the best interest of a virus to kill the majority of the individuals/hosts that it infects. It is considered somewhat suicidal, as it will ultimately kill off the majority of potential hosts.

For a map of Italy, see http://healthmap.org/r/79yP. - Mod.MPP]
